Color variation in preservative (~ 70 % ethanol): Topotypic specimens and one from a nearby site (
KU 169268
) (
4 females
,
7 males
) are similar to the holotype . Dorsal color generally varies from pale creamy brown (
KU
200217
) to dark brown (
KU
200212
); spiculae and coni vary from dark brown to black. A male (
KU
200216
) has dark brown marbling on the dorsum, and stripes at joints on the tarsi, feet and hands. The venter is uniform cream in all individuals. A thin brown line along middorsum varies from conspicuous (
KU
200207
) to barely visible (
KU
200217
).

